{
  "genre": "rock",
  "mode": "focus",
  "mixStrategy": "This rock focus arrangement in Em uses a I-bVII-IV progression (Em-D-Am) cycling every 8 beats (6.4s). The energy arc builds from 0.4\u21920.6\u21920.7\u21920.7\u21920.7\u21920.5 across six ~7.5s segments.\n\nFREQUENCY SEPARATION: Bass (Electric Bass, MIDI 28-47) anchors 20-300Hz with driving eighth-note root patterns that lock tightly with the kick drum. Chords (Warm Pad, MIDI 50-67) fill 300Hz-2kHz with sustained power chord voicings (root+5th) providing harmonic warmth. Melody (Overdriven Guitar, MIDI 60-76) occupies 1-8kHz with pentatonic riffs using moderate note lengths (1-3s) for focus-friendly predictability. Drums provide the rhythmic skeleton: kick on 1&3, snare on 2&4, hi-hat eighths throughout.\n\nRHYTHMIC INTERLOCK: Bass and kick drum hit together on beats 1 and 3, creating a tight low-end pulse. Snare accents on 2&4 provide the backbeat. Melody phrases breathe between snare hits, landing chord tones on strong beats. The pad sustains underneath everything, gluing the harmony together.\n\nENERGY ARC: Segments 1 (0-7.5s) starts sparse with lower velocities. Segments 2-3 (7.5-22.5s) add density and velocity. Segments 4-5 (22.5-37.5s) maintain peak focus energy. Segment 6 (37.5-45s) pulls back for a gentle wind-down. All tracks follow the same Em-D-Am progression, changing chords together on the same beats throughout.",
